<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06038j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06038j">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06038j"> 38(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> branch = snake / mist = ghost / tree = giant</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Les diverses illusions des sens sont un exemple frappant de cette intervention de l&apos;imagination dans la perception. <mark>Un buisson fait au peureux l&apos;effet d&apos;un brigand</mark> en embuscade, un l&eacute;ger <mark>brouillard est pris pour un fant&ocirc;me</mark>, une <mark>branche d&apos;arbre pour un serpent</mark>. <font color="green">[The various illusions of the senses are a striking example of this intervention of the imagination in perception. A bush makes the fearful effect of a robber in ambush, a light fog is mistaken for a ghost, a branch of a tree for a snake.]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 4</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c01108g" href="c01all.htm#c01108g">VI.C.01:108(g)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
